Hi all, I've taken CS 188, 189 and data science 100 and i really enjoy the DS100 course given how practical it is. I was wondering if there are any other courses out there that are similar to DS 100 (i heard IEOR 135 is a super interesting and practical course too) in terms of applied ML ? Also, I know that some schools offer classes that teach data mining, and building recommender systems specifically, and I was wondering if there are courses here at Cal that cover building recommender systems?

Thanks!
history.subject: Recommender systems and Data mining
